# Protocol Spec: shielded_vote_book

The canonical protocol specification lives in the `shielded_vote_book/` directory (symlinked from an external Obsidian vault). A committed index at `docs/shielded-vote-book-index.md` summarizes every file in the book.

## Reading protocol docs

1. Read `docs/shielded-vote-book-index.md` first to find the relevant file(s).
2. Then read the specific file(s) from `shielded_vote_book/`.
3. Do NOT ingest the entire book for a single question.

## Keeping the index accurate

If you read a file from `shielded_vote_book/` and notice any of the following, update `docs/shielded-vote-book-index.md` immediately:

- A file listed in the index no longer exists or has been renamed
- New files exist that aren't in the index
- A file's content no longer matches its index summary
- Sections have been restructured

Also update the index when writing to the book (new files, restructured sections, significantly changed content).

## If the symlink is missing

If `shielded_vote_book/` does not exist, tell the user:

> The `shielded_vote_book` symlink is not present. Please create it:
> ```
> ln -s /path/to/your/shielded_vote_book shielded_vote_book
> ```
> See `docs/ai_setup.md` for details.
